Century Global Commodities Corporation 			 



 You are here:  Home   /   Social Responsibility   /  Environmental Responsibility Environmental Responsibility 

 Century is committed to accountability for environmental stewardship by meeting or exceeding legislative requirements. 
 Our goals include: 

 Measuring performance against continually improving environmental targets; 
 Minimizing adverse environmental impacts; 
 Reporting significant environmental incidents; 
 Complying with legislation, regulations, standards and codes of practice; 
 Involving regulators and local communities; and 
 Rehabilitation during operations and after project closure. 

 We will: 

 Implement monitoring and control of environmental aspects; 
 Minimize adverse environmental impacts; 
 Educate  employees, contractors and suppliers to ensure alignment with our environmental goals; 
 Monitor compliance and performance; 
 Remediate disturbed areas; 
 Require guidelines from contractors and suppliers to reduce usage, recycle materials and to ensure compliance with both regulations and  our standards; 
 Consult with local communities and other stakeholders to verify our performance; 
 Provide financial security as required to rehabilitate project disturbances; and 
 Develop actions to respond to an incident and plans to avoid reoccurrence. 

